127 A.3d 562 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. Mark R. GALBRAITH. Misc. Docket AG No. 33,

Sept. Term, 2015.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Dec. 16, 2015.

ORDER

The Court having considered the petition for disciplinary or remedial action filed in the above entitled matter in accordance with Md. Rules 16—751(a)(2) and 16—773(b), the response to the show cause order filed by Bar Counsel, and there being no response filed by the Respondent, it is this 16th day of December, 2015

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the petition be, and it is hereby, granted, and Mark R. Galbraith is disbarred, effective immediately, from the practice of law in this State subject to further order of this Court; and it is further

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall forthwith strike the name of Mark R. Galbraith from the register of *379attorneys in this Court and shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State in accordance with Rule 16-760(e).
